# Collection

Utility data structure used in Discord.js.
<p>A Map with additional utility methods: A Map with additional utility methods. This is used throughout discord.js rather than Arrays for anything that has an ID, for significantly improved performance and ease-of-use.
<p>Cached array for the <code>array()</c: Cached array for the array() method - will be reset to null whenever set() or delete() are called
<p>Cached array for the <code>keyArray(): Cached array for the keyArray() method - will be reset to null whenever set() or delete() are called
<p>Creates an ordered array of the value: Creates an ordered array of the values of this collection, and caches it internally. The array will only be reconstructed if an item is added to or removed from the collection, or if you change the length of the array itself. If you don't want this caching behavior, use [...collection.values()] or Array.from(collection.values()) instead.
<p>Creates an ordered array of the keys: Creates an ordered array of the keys of this collection, and caches it internally. The array will only be reconstructed if an item is added to or removed from the collection, or if you change the length of the array itself. If you don't want this caching behavior, use [...collection.keys()] or Array.from(collection.keys()) instead.
<p>Obtains the first value(s) in this co: Obtains the first value(s) in this collection.
<p>Amount of values to obtain from the b: Amount of values to obtain from the beginning
<p>A single value if no amount is provid: A single value if no amount is provided or an array of values, starting from the end if amount is negative
<p>Obtains the first key(s) in this coll: Obtains the first key(s) in this collection.
<p>Amount of keys to obtain from the beg: Amount of keys to obtain from the beginning
<p>A single key if no amount is provided: A single key if no amount is provided or an array of keys, starting from the end if amount is negative
<p>Obtains the last value(s) in this col: Obtains the last value(s) in this collection. This relies on {@link Collection#array}, and thus the caching mechanism applies here as well.
<p>Amount of values to obtain from the e: Amount of values to obtain from the end
<p>A single value if no amount is provid: A single value if no amount is provided or an array of values, starting from the start if amount is negative
<p>Obtains the last key(s) in this colle: Obtains the last key(s) in this collection. This relies on {@link Collection#keyArray}, and thus the caching mechanism applies here as well.
<p>Amount of keys to obtain from the end: Amount of keys to obtain from the end
<p>A single key if no amount is provided: A single key if no amount is provided or an array of keys, starting from the start if amount is negative
<p>Obtains unique random value(s) from t: Obtains unique random value(s) from this collection. This relies on {@link Collection#array}, and thus the caching mechanism applies here as well.
<p>A single value if no amount is provid: A single value if no amount is provided or an array of values
<p>Obtains unique random key(s) from thi: Obtains unique random key(s) from this collection. This relies on {@link Collection#keyArray}, and thus the caching mechanism applies here as well.
<p>A single key if no amount is provided: A single key if no amount is provided or an array
<p>Searches for a single item where the: Searches for a single item where the given function returns a truthy value. This behaves like Array.find(). All collections used in Discord.js are mapped using their id property, and if you want to find by id you should use the get method. See MDN for details.
<p>The function to test with (should ret: The function to test with (should return boolean)
<p>Value to use as <code>this</code> whe: Value to use as this when executing function
<p>Searches for the key of a single item: Searches for the key of a single item where the given function returns a truthy value. This behaves like Array.findIndex(), but returns the key rather than the positional index.
<p>Removes entries that satisfy the prov: Removes entries that satisfy the provided filter function.
<p>Function used to test (should return: Function used to test (should return a boolean)
<p>Identical to\n<a href=\"https://devel: Identical to Array.filter(), but returns a Collection instead of an Array.
<p>Partitions the collection into two co: Partitions the collection into two collections where the first collection contains the items that passed and the second contains the items that failed.
<p>Maps each item into a Collection, the: Maps each item into a Collection, then joins the results into a single Collection. Identical in behavior to Array.flatMap().
<p>Maps each item to another value into: Maps each item to another value into an array. Identical in behavior to Array.map().
<p>Function that produces an element of: Function that produces an element of the new array, taking three arguments
<p>Maps each item to another value into: Maps each item to another value into a collection. Identical in behavior to Array.map().
<p>Function that produces an element of: Function that produces an element of the new collection, taking three arguments
<p>Checks if there exists an item that p: Checks if there exists an item that passes a test. Identical in behavior to Array.some().
<p>Checks if all items passes a test. Id: Checks if all items passes a test. Identical in behavior to Array.every().
<p>Applies a function to produce a singl: Applies a function to produce a single value. Identical in behavior to Array.reduce().
<p>Function used to reduce, taking four: Function used to reduce, taking four arguments; accumulator, currentValue, currentKey, and collection
<p>Identical to\n<a href=\"https://devel: Identical to Map.forEach(), but returns the collection instead of undefined.
<p>Runs a function on the collection and: Runs a function on the collection and returns the collection.
<p>Creates an identical shallow copy of: Creates an identical shallow copy of this collection.
<p>Combines this collection with others: Combines this collection with others into a new collection. None of the source collections are modified.
<p>Checks if this collection shares iden: Checks if this collection shares identical key-value pairings with another. This is different to checking for equality using equal-signs, because the collections may be different objects, but contain the same data.
<p>The sort method sorts the elements of: The sort method sorts the elements of a collection in place and returns it. The sort is not necessarily stable. The default sort order is according to string Unicode code points.
<p>Specifies a function that defines the: Specifies a function that defines the sort order. If omitted, the collection is sorted according to each character's Unicode code point value, according to the string conversion of each element.
<p>The sorted method sorts the elements: The sorted method sorts the elements of a collection and returns it. The sort is not necessarily stable. The default sort order is according to string Unicode code points.
